@rica with this ticket, I'm pretty sure the client was just seeing a cached version of the page FYI. Let's see if my response below works for her. Thanks

Hi Martina,

Sure, it appears you have made the changes correctly, but may just have been seeing a 'cached' version of the page. If every you can see two different versions of the website in different browsers, 99% of the time it means that one of the browsers is loading and old version of the page (a cached version). In this instance, if you clear your browsers cache you should be seeing an accurate and most recent version of the page.

Hope that clears it up? Let me know if you have any further questions?
